The idea is to be able to have ipv4 and ipv6 details, unfortunatelly I full ipv6 adress w/o abbreviations won't fit the input field so it have to be "ellipsized"
The first time "Use as HotSpot" is switched on the SSID and passoword are autogenerated, the user can ghange them.
The password should be pronunciable. If the user deletes the password the network would be open.
Once activated the settings should be stored and ripristinated every time this mode is active.
The ip is automaically set as the first ip in a free network intervall. Every time hotspot mode is switched on the system should verify the network interval
is not used, if it is pick another one automagically.
We may use a notification to inform the user about what's happen when switching on Use as HotSpot.
With everything set as automatic it works exacylt like automatic mode. Here is possible to manually set the network interval and ip to use.
Do we need to have security configurable here? Some clients for example don't like adhoc netoworks and WPA, like the mac IIRC.
Clicking will bring up the dialog, if IPv6 is set to be configured automatically,
but it got no address, it should report "Enabled". Otherwise it should show
the address in the form of <address>/<prefix length> or "Disabled".
IPv4 only, I see no need to support IPv6 here, am I wrong?
